    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="features-grid"
            width="32"
            height="32"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path
              d="M 32 0 L 0 0 0 32"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#features-grid)"></rect>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Reschedule Appointments Visually Without Forms
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Drag-and-drop management transforms calendar editing from tedious
            form-filling into natural visual interaction. Instead of clicking
            edit buttons, changing times in dropdown menus, and confirming
            updates, you simply click an appointment and drag it to the new time
            slot. The appointment moves instantly with smooth animation showing
            exactly where it will land. This visual approach reduces
            rescheduling from multiple clicks and form interactions down to a
            single drag gesture, making calendar adjustments feel effortless
            rather than administrative.
          </p>

          <p>
            Conflict detection works automatically during dragging. When you
            move an appointment over an occupied time slot, visual feedback
            immediately shows the overlap with red highlighting or warning
            indicators. This real-time conflict awareness prevents
            double-booking before you drop the appointment, eliminating the
            error state that traditional form-based scheduling creates when you
            submit conflicting times. You see scheduling problems instantly
            while dragging rather than discovering them after clicking save
            buttons.
          </p>

          <p>
            Duration adjustments work through edge dragging. Each appointment
            displays resize handles on top and bottom edges. Drag the bottom
            edge down to extend meeting duration or drag the top edge to adjust
            start time while keeping end time fixed. This visual manipulation
            makes duration changes feel like physical objects you are reshaping
            rather than abstract time values you are entering in forms. When a
            meeting runs long or needs buffer time added, extending the
            appointment takes one drag gesture instead of navigating edit
            dialogs.
          </p>

          <p>
            Changes save automatically without confirmation dialogs. When you
            drop an appointment in a new location, CalendHub immediately updates
            the calendar and syncs changes to connected services. Undo
            functionality provides safety net for accidental moves, letting you
            reverse changes with one click if you drag the wrong appointment or
            drop in unintended location. This combination of instant saves and
            easy undo creates confident editing environment where you can
            quickly adjust schedules without worrying about irreversible
            mistakes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
